<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="persuade-vt">persuade <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /pə'sweɪd/    美 /pər'sweɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-convince">1.★ <strong>使相信；使信服 (convince)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>persuade sb of sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m persuaded of his honesty. 
我相信他是诚实的。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>persuade sb + that 从句:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I persuaded him that I was telling the truth. 
我使他相信我讲的是实情。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-talk-into">2.★ <strong>说服；劝服 (talk into)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is always easily persuaded. 
她总是很容易被说服。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>persuade sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She persuaded me to go to a dental school.
她说服了我去牙科学校学习。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>persuade sb into (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I managed to persuade my classmates into accepting my idea.
我设法说服了我的同学接受我的想法。</p><footer>2015 浙江书面表达</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>persuade sb out of (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We persuaded him out of his foolish plan. 
我们说服了他放弃那项愚蠢的计划。</p></div>

<p>注: 在表示“劝说”，但不一定“劝服”时，用try to persuade。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She would try to persuade local business leaders to contribute money to the cause.
她会劝说当地的商界领导人为该事业捐款。</p><footer>2017 北京改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>persuasion /pə'sweɪʒn/ n [U] <br />
persuasive /pə'sweɪsɪv/ adj   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>If she doesn’t want to go, nothing you can say will <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (说服) her.  （2012 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. persuade  </p></div>